'''Ntfsprogs''' is a collection of [[Free software|free]] [[Unix]] utilities for managing the [[NTFS]] [[filesystem]] used by [[Windows XP]], [[Windows Server 2003]], [[Windows 2000]], [[Windows NT 4.0]], [[Windows Vista]], [[Windows Server 2008]] and [[Windows 7]] on a [[Partition (computing)|harddisk partition]]. 'ntfsprogs' was the first stable method of writing to NTFS partitions in Linux.<ref>{{Citation | last = Shilliday | first = Barry | publication-date = 2007-04-17 | title = Running other operating systems alongside Linux | periodical = [[Personal Computer World]] | url = http://www.pcw.co.uk/personal-computer-world/features/2187957/hands-running-operating-systems | accessdate = 2008-05-29 }}</ref>
All NTFS versions are supported, used by 32-bit and 64-bit Windows. ntfsprogs remains a popular way of interacting with NTFS partitions and is included by most [[Linux]] distributions<ref>{{Citation | last = Mathes | first = Steven | publication-date = 2007-02-01 | title = The Interoperability Power of Linux-NTFS Tools | periodical = [[Linux Journal]] | url = http://www.linuxjournal.com/article/9327 | accessdate = 2008-05-29 }}</ref> and on [[Live CD]]s. There are also versions that have been compiled for Windows.
On April 12, 2011 it was announced that Ntfsprogs project was merged with [[NTFS-3G]].<ref>[http://www.tuxera.com/open-source/release-ntfs-3g-ntfsprogs-2011-4-12/]</ref>
==Included programs== * <tt>[[ntfsresize]]</tt>, used for non-destructively resizing a NTFS Partition * <tt>[[ntfsclone]]</tt>, used for making uncompressed, but space-efficient [[disk cloning|clones]] of NTFS Partitions. It does not support image verification{{Citation needed|date=February 2011}}. * <tt>mkntfs</tt>, used for creating NTFS partitions * <tt>ntfsmount</tt>, for [[mount (computing)|mounting]] using [[Filesystem in Userspace|FUSE]] * <tt>ntfsfix</tt>, schedules a Windows check of a file system on the next boot * <tt>ntfsundelete</tt>, undeletes a file * <tt>ntfsdecrypt</tt>, decrypts [[Encrypting File System|EFS]] * <tt>ntfsck</tt>, performs a consistency check on the specified volume. (Note that development appears to be suspended.<ref>{{Citation | last= Altaparmakov | first = Anton | publication-date = 2009-03-12 | title = Ntfsprogs - ntfsck | periodical = none | url = http://www.nabble.com/Ntfsprogs---ntfsck-td22472614.html | accessdate = 2009-05-16 }}</ref>)
Other programs are included, but are very basic in functionality, and/or intended for developers.
